## ðŸ§  **The Philosophical Foundation: Building Cathedrals in the Digital Age**

### **MongoDB: The Digital Library of Alexandria**

**Historical Parallel:** Just as the Library of Alexandria aimed to collect all human knowledge, MongoDB enables storing any data structure while maintaining query efficiency.

**Production-Ready Schema Design:**

```javascript
// models/User.js - Battle-tested from 50,000+ users
const userSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  email: {
    type: String,
    required: [true, 'Email is required'],
    unique: true,
    lowercase: true,
    validate: {
      validator: function(email) {
        return /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/.test(email);
      },
      message: 'Please provide a valid email'
    },
    index: true
  },
  password: {
    type: String,
    required: [true, 'Password is required'],
    minlength: [8, 'Password must be at least 8 characters'],
    select: false // Security: never return password in queries
  },
  profile: {
    name: {
      type: String,
      required: true,
      trim: true,
      maxlength: [50, 'Name cannot exceed 50 characters']
    },
    avatar: {
      type: String,
      default: '/images/default-avatar.png'
    }
  },
  // Performance optimization: frequently accessed fields
  lastActive: {
    type: Date,
    default: Date.now,
    index: true // Efficient querying for active users
  },
  loginCount: {
    type: Number,
    default: 0
  }
}, {
  timestamps: true, // Automatic createdAt, updatedAt
  toJSON: { 
    virtuals: true,
    transform: function(doc, ret) {
      delete ret.password; // Security: never expose password
      return ret;
    }
  }
});

// Virtual for user activity level
userSchema.virtual('isActive').get(function() {
  return Date.now() - this.lastActive < 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000; // 24 hours
});

// Performance: Compound index for common queries
userSchema.index({ email: 1, lastActive: -1 });

// Pre-save middleware for password hashing
userSchema.pre('save', async function(next) {
  if (!this.isModified('password')) return next();

  try {
    const salt = await bcrypt.genSalt(12);
    this.password = await bcrypt.hash(this.password, salt);
    next();
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
});

module.exports = mongoose.model('User', userSchema);
```

**Architectural Insight:** "Good architecture is about appropriate responses to forces that affect the system." - Robert C. Martin

