## 10. Private Methods and Fields

Enhanced class privacy:

```javascript
class User {
  #password; // Private field
  #attempts = 0; // Private field with initial value

  constructor(username, password) {
    this.username = username;
    this.#password = this.#hashPassword(password);
  }

  // Private method
  #hashPassword(password) {
    return crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', 
      new TextEncoder().encode(password)
    );
  }

  // Private static method
  static #validateUsername(username) {
    return username.length >= 3;
  }

  // Public method that uses private fields/methods
  async login(password) {
    if (this.#attempts >= 3) {
      throw new Error('Too many login attempts');
    }

    const hashed = await this.#hashPassword(password);
    if (hashed === this.#password) {
      this.#attempts = 0;
      return true;
    }

    this.#attempts++;
    return false;
  }

  static create(username, password) {
    if (!this.#validateUsername(username)) {
      throw new Error('Invalid username');
    }
    return new User(username, password);
  }
}

// Usage
const user = User.create('john_doe', 'securepassword');
```

